{"id":14881672,"mediaExerciseId":"95306a72-258e-4726-8727-6f7841d3d2e7","exerciseName":"8","chapterName":"19","chapterTitle":"Cash and Liquidity Management","groupId":612446,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":659,"solutions":[{"id":6005005,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"Notice that, when a firm has an available balance at a bank greater than the book balance, it leads to a disbursement float. \nHere a firm has a book balance of $\\$2$ million, and a bank balance is $\\$2.5$. Therefore, the firm has written checks that have not yet been collected. Thus, the payment activities of the company (writing checks) generate float payments.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Since a bank balance is greater than book balance, firm's position is \n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Disbursement float}&=\\text{ Firm’s available balance}-\\text{ Firm’s book balance}\\\\\n&=\\$2.5\\hspace{2mm}\\text{million}-\\$2\\hspace{2mm}\\text{million}\\\\\n&=\\$500,000\n\\end{align*}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/9b9192e269c13f23244cc44a88eb3721/c5b5546106ca48d6c761105332602c73/lateximg_large.png","width":645},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/9b9192e269c13f23244cc44a88eb3721/c5b5546106ca48d6c761105332602c73/lateximg.png","width":322}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"So, disbursement float is $\\$500,000$ and that means that the bank thinks that the company owns an amount that is $\\$500,000$ more than its actual available amount of money. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/9b9192e269c13f23244cc44a88eb3721/e2647fc1ef68b7aaa9850cc18f263219/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":92,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/9b9192e269c13f23244cc44a88eb3721/e2647fc1ef68b7aaa9850cc18f263219/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"6dd452ba-cf13-46d9-b8bb-65436a1e8072","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881673,"exerciseName":"9","page":659,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d778f330-9b4b-48e6-9255-dcb8bbb6520d","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-19-critical-thinking-questions-9-d778f330-9b4b-48e6-9255-dcb8bbb6520d"},{"id":14881674,"exerciseName":"10","page":659,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"91b807d8-5b55-4834-8a61-2b97663a4719","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-19-critical-thinking-questions-10-91b807d8-5b55-4834-8a61-2b97663a4719"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881671,"exerciseName":"7","page":659,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"dc3ed9e0-02e2-49e7-b2c7-20386e2a8d8d","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fu